Rule #18: &ldquo;Never forget about depreciation.&rdquo;
 You can refuse the usefulness of this rule but you can never refuse the existence of depreciation expense.
Oftentimes depreciation expense takes up a significant portion of a cost that is being used. Here is an example related to car ownership. It makes my hair move just looking at this graph. In other words, that is how depreciation deceitfully hides in cost.

Rule #15: &ldquo;Always go an extra mile in preparation for important events. Do a little more.&rdquo; 1
There is always a margin for error in preparations similar to those in mathematical calculations. An extra effort will allow you to minimize the error effects.
